siteProductLine.name: Farm Specialist R-1
siteProductLine.overview:
The Carlstar/Carlisle Farm Specialist R-1 is an all-purpose tractor tire specially designed for superior traction and lateral stability. It features a unique multi-angle long bar design which allows you to maintain traction and stability on the most challenging surfaces. Applicable for a variety of soil conditions, the Carlstar/Carlisle Farm Specialist R-1™s extra reinforced tread lugs and overlapping center tread lugs deliver strength and power so you can go through wet and dry soil. This versatile tire ensures that your performance isn™t compromised even as you use it on different applications such as agriculture and construction. No need to worry about damage as this tire is designed for withstanding wear. Not only that but it also provides comfort so you don™t have to feel worn down even after driving the whole day. Carlstar/Carlisle Tire is best known for producing the best ATV tires in the united states. Founded in 1917 AT Carlstar/Carlisle, PA by Charles Moomy, the company has become one of the most well-known tire manufacturers for their dedication to building long-lasting high quality tires.

Features & Benefits
  • Superior traction that allows you to use the tire on several surfaces and applications
  • Its versatile nature allows you to use it in various ways without worry about premature wear
  • Comfortable to drive in so you can work in peace
  • Carlisle branded tires are now Carlstar, and offer the same excellent performance, durability, and value that they have for the past 100 years

siteProductSpecs.name: Vehicle
siteProductSpecs.description: Designed for use on tractors, sprayers, harvesters, trailers, implement control, and other farm equipment. These tires are typically designed to reduce soil compaction, resist damage, and provide high flotation so that drivers don't sink in soft surfaces.

siteProductSpecs.name: Mileage Warranty
siteProductSpecs.description: This product is not covered by a manufacturer’s treadlife warranty.

siteProductSpecs.name: Load Range
siteProductSpecs.description: The maximum load carrying strength at the specified inflation pressure, also known as ply rating.

siteProductSpecs.name: Sidewall
siteProductSpecs.description: The side of the tire between the tread and rim, with cosmetic branding as well as information about the tire including manufacturer, model, size, etc.

siteProductSpecs.name: Inflation Pressure
siteProductSpecs.description: The highest inflation pressure (measured in pounds of force per square inch, PSI) the tire is designed to contain, and should only be used when called for by the vehicle placard.

siteProductSpecs.name: Part Number
siteProductSpecs.description: An identifier of a particular tire line and size combination assigned by the tire manufacturer.

siteProductSpecs.name: Section Width
siteProductSpecs.description: The measurement of width from a tires inner sidewall to the outer sidewall.

siteProductSpecs.name: Overall Diameter
siteProductSpecs.description: The diameter of a tire that is inflated without any load applied.

siteDynamicModal.title: Oversized Tires.
siteDynamicModal.content: We offer fast shipping on every tire shipped to an installer partner or FedEx pickup location. A nominal shipping fee will be added for oversized tires (typically larger farm, commercial and industrial sizes). Learn more about your delivery options in our FAQ.
